<TITLE> Jalil admitted to Mount Elizabeth in Singapore </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 04 (bdnews24.com) - Awami League general secretary Abdul Jalil has been admitted to Mount Elizabeth Hospital in Singapore, an AL spokesperson said. AL deputy publicity secretary Ashim Kumar Ukil said Jalil arrived in the city state early Tuesday morning, and was rushed by ambulance straight from the airport to the hospital. The treatment of the AL leader began as soon as he reached Mount Elizabeth Hospital in Singapore, Ukil told bdnews24.com Tuesday. "I contacted Singapore by telephone. Jalil has been admitted to hospital and the doctors have begun tests." Jalil, accompanied by his wife, left Dhaka on a Singapore Airlines flight shortly before midnight Monday. Security had been tightened in and around Zia International Airport ahead of their flight. The AL leader"critically" ill with heart and kidney ailmentswas released on one-month parole Sunday with a series of conditions attached, after a medical board at LabAid hospital recommended medical treatment overseas. bdnews24.c
